                        size="3"><b>A thought for today<br>
                        </b>It is not necessarily true that averaging
                        the averages of different populations gives the
                        average of the combined population. (Simpson's
                        Paradox) -Edward H. SIMPSON, statistician (b.
                        1922)<br>
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        <b>A second one<br>
                        </b>The lust for comfort murders the passions of
                        the soul - Khalil GIBRAN, mystic, poet, and
                        artist (1883-1931)<br>
                        <br>
                        <br>
                        <b>And a third one<br>
                        </b>No iron spike can pierce a human heart as
                        icily as a period in the right place - Isaac
                        BABEL, author (1894-1940)</font></p>
